OL,3,CD-Day 80 The Last Veterans: Pam Harding
OL,5,FMrs Harding said: "It was a big
OL,6,Frambling house.
OL,8,F"There were quite a lot of us there,
OL,9,Fand we learned how to work a radio.
OL,10,FHow to work interception and which
OL,11,Fknobs to twiddle - and also, of
OL,12,Fcourse, we learned quite a lot of
OL,13,FGerman naval phraseology, such as
OL,14,F'Full speed aft'".
OL,16,FThere were about 50- 60 people working
OL,17,Fthere according to a news release from
OL,18,FGCHQ marking the organisation's 100th
OL,19,Fanniversary.
