OL,3,CD-Day 80 The Last Veterans: Pam Harding
OL,5,FIt read: "This base collected Very
OL,6,FHigh Frequency (VHF) communications
OL,7,Ffrom Germany directing aircraft or
OL,8,Ffast moving E-boats in the English
OL,9,FChannel. VHF has a very short range
OL,10,Fwhich meant that German linguists,
OL,11,Fmainly young women, were sent to the
OL,12,Ffront line to live log the
OL,13,Fcommunications. This type of
OL,14,Finterception had never been done
OL,15,Fbefore for voice communications and
OL,16,Fthe tactical nature of this job meant
OL,17,Fthat every day the information
OL,18,Fcollected by these young women was
OL,19,Fhelping to protect British pilots and
OL,20,Fsailors. German forces would try to
OL,21,Fcapture British pilots downed over the
OL,22,FChannel and information from Abbots
OL,23,FCliff House would have helped to save
OL,24,Fsome British pilots during the war."
